From aa0dcaa44e2f6b2726d6e71f80f04c1be35c5f71 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 18:34:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] EXPERIMENT E-UNION: route getdirentries through paged merged
 readdir (PoC, #ifdef EUNION)

Add vchroot_getdents_merge(fd, out, cap): a paged producer that returns the
MERGED directory listing (upper wins, lower template merged in, whiteouts
subtracted, opaque honoured) as linux_dirent64 records, so getdirentries sees
the union view. It materializes the full merged listing ONCE per open dir fd
(reusing the proven vchroot_readdir_merge enumeration) into a small per-fd
buffer, then hands it out page by page -- sidestepping getdents64 rewind/
pagination hazards entirely.

Per-fd state is keyed by fd number, so it MUST be freed before the fd is
recycled: vchroot_dir_closed(fd) is now called from sys_close_nocancel() and
close_internal(). The hermetic test caught this contract (fd-reuse returned a
stale exhausted cursor -> empty listing) before it could bite in production.

Wire sys_getdirentries / sys_getdirentries64 to call the merge instead of raw
getdents64 (both #ifdef EUNION; #else keeps the exact baseline call).

Also fixes the on-wire dirent64 record size: use offsetof(...,d_name), not
sizeof(struct linux_dirent64), since a copy of that struct in scope declares a
fixed d_name[256] (sizeof was 280, overflowing every page). The hermetic
many-page test (40 lower + 40 upper + 10 in-both, drained through a 256B page
buffer) exercises this and the cross-page dedup.

All #ifdef EUNION -> production byte-identical (verified: zero E-UNION symbols
without the flag). experiments/e-union now 67 assertions, green & stable.

Local only, nothing pushed.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
